snippet.textDisplay: There is no way the 3990X will cost anything less than $4k. It will demand a price premium over the 3970X due to the value of the performance per socket/system. You must also consider the EPYC 7702P ($5k), EPYC 7702 ($7k), and EPYC 7742 ($8k), which are clocked much lower with only a 20% lower TDP. It will be far more powerful than the 7702P, but it will have to be cost-competitive with 2X 7702/7742 chips. I do not see it selling for less than $6k.
snippet.textOriginal: There is no way the 3990X will cost anything less than $4k. It will demand a price premium over the 3970X due to the value of the performance per socket/system. You must also consider the EPYC 7702P ($5k), EPYC 7702 ($7k), and EPYC 7742 ($8k), which are clocked much lower with only a 20% lower TDP.
